I recently shared some advice with a fren of mine with the common complaint of no longer being able to find videos on YouTube because they are deleted, banned, or restricted by the increasingly out-of-control censorship algorithms. And I realized that I should probably share this information with more people who are pissed off with this BULLSHIT! 1) open TOR browser. For those who don't have it or have never heard of it, it's free, download it! torproject.org 2) Search for the topic or title of the video in the browser, NOT ON THE YOUTUBE ENGINE. 3) Select "videos" from the results menu. 4) Scroll and find the videos you thought were deleted or banned. 5) Download them and save them while you still can. This method is successful because the censorship or banning of videos on YouTube is almost entirely a function of the YouTube search algorithms. In most cases, NOT ALL, the videos are still stored on the google servers and are only restricted by internet "Great firewall" settings in country you are searching from. *Top Tip* If you still can't find what you are looking for, choose "new identity" from the dropdown menu on TOR. This will select a new country of origin in which there may be no restrictions for the content you are looking for. I hope this is of value to you, sorry I haven't shared this with everyone before.
